treasureMemories.description: This keyboard helped unlock my true potential
Gene used to play this thing all the time, it was the soundtrack of our childhood.
Aw, my baby's keyboard! Mommy's proud of you Genie-weenie!
Louise hated when we tried to tell her she was too old for this toy.
Moolissa came to me in my dreams!
She once stared down the driver of a car - oh that cow is silly!
She really didn't want to go back down the stairs after she came into the house.
I support your mother's... interesting ideas.
Aw, Bobby was so cute when he was showing Mr. Fishoeder my invention!
I let the charm bomb explode with this one.
I waved my heart out with those flags on race day!
Tina and I had our differences, but we settled them in the end.
Louise's ass was grass, and I was gonna mow it - until I remembered we're family.
I liked being part of the Thundergirls!
Me and Gene had to help Tina find those sneaky Thundergirls who were stealing cookies!
Louise was a great Thundergirl in training.
Oh! We used that spatula for .... something different.

It's not really that long of a story: Jeff was an Easy Breezy brand shoe box with the name "Jeff" written on it. Tina thought Jeff was a ghost who lived inside the box, but I tricked her in to thinking he was a 13-year-old boy, after an exterminator said there was a ghost in the restaurant. Thinking he was a boy, Tina started a relationship with Jeff and took him to a Butterfly exhibit, a park, Wonder Wharf and to school.
I just loved having a seance with my babies for Jeff!
Ooh, I found another picture from our seance!
I definitely found my happy place
Yep, there's Dad, prancing around the garden while we watched the restaurant. And with Logan's mom... yuck.
Dad looks so happy here.
I don't care what anyone says. I look good in that hat.
The upgrade we fought with the guy at the store about!
Right before the collision that started the wild goosechase...
SO MUCH SITTING
SO MUCH EATING ON THAT COUCH!!
This board was built to help me prove I belonged at the adult table for the holidays, but it proved far more useful in the long run.
It was such an important memory that poor Bobby was in denial about her growing up, and we spent a lot of money on multiple turkeys one Thanksgiving!
That's not even the best picture of my work!
I mean, Louise is a little scary, but she helped catch my criminal when it was ... me, so... yeah, she's good at what she does.
Aw, I loved that sign!
This was one of the best memories I have with Tina and Gene, defending what's ours.
I remember Pony Danza and the other Bronies!
That was not how I saw my weekend at Equestra Con going, but it turned out pretty good.
Birdseye view of the accident.
A picture from better times - like 90 seconds before it all went wrong
The Aftermath - it wasn't pretty, that's true.
I enjoyed cooking with you guys as kids.
It was weird that it was painted, and even weirder that we hung it up in the kitchen.
Wasn't that the same year as the Totoro Turkey? Or ... was that a fever dream I had because of the absinthe? Never mind.
We didn't get to attend, as we had to decline the invitation.
Um, this thing has seen more than just a grill!
Mom and Dad may not know about our time on the ferry to the neighborhood with full-size candy bars!
Oh, how I loved plotting for candy!
It was always so fun to see your loot after an evening of trick-or-treating!
The maps we made were so impressive - I hate that we didn't get to use it that year!
I think someone else was more in love with them, particularly BooBoo...
Tina, no one knows what you're talking about...
Ohhhhkkaaayyyy, Louise ....
Remember the good times?
BOO BOO!!
Tina, sweetie, you write such great stories! A little steamy, but hey, everyone deserves to find their Tom Selleck!
Oh, those were spicy days.
I really loved coming up with the burgers.
I just needed to get it out of my system, that's all.
Who are we kidding, those girls were never going to make it in showbiz!
I thought Gene was going to have a come-apart with them.
Girls being girls being girls being girls might be some of Gene's best work.
They weren't the worst thing she ever brought home, but they definitely weren't the best.
Ooh, I loved being in charge of driving!
Dad didn't think our jokes were too funny.
People seemed to really like eating from our smaller, grosser kitchen on wheels
I played it for so long
Yeah, Dad wasn't too happy when Jimmy's Dad got the high score.
I prefer not to game where I work, thank YOU!
Ooh, some steamy memories, right Bobby?
Lin, that was a dream you had. But yes, we all were happy to ride the ice cream wave that summer.
I STILL scream for Ice Cream!
Yes, we were the talk of the block that season!
And here's another photo of my old man's shop.
Yes, one of our favorite things to do together.
I watched with Dad too!
We did spend hours watching it together.
Dad was NOT pleased when she hung them up in the store for the art crawl!
Mom was just looking out for Aunt Gayle though!
And it definitely got us in the creative and entrepreneurial spirit!
Dad wouldn't give him back once I let him borrow him!
Kuchi Kopi and I went through a harrowing adventure together.
Aw, yeah, these hung in the hall!
I love you guys
I forgot about this!
From when Dad left him in the walk-in!
DAD KILLED HIM!
Here's a photo of "the incident"
That was a hard night.
I was so proud of my babies working together, they stayed up all night to get it built!
Teddy helped us get across the finish line.
Louise didn't want to quit
Here's the MOOSE! It's NOT a reindeer, so don't ever call it that. We had it since Tina was a baby.
I can't believe we tried to get rid of it!
I loved building pillow forts with this couch!
This cat and I had a love-hate relationship
Aunt Gayle sure loved that cat.
Was it weird she brought him to the restaurant? No, probably not.
I'm glad we got to sit on it outside, though!
He definitely had a power struggle with me. I think he won.
He really loved that show. It was a little strange.
It was the best. show. EVER.
Aw, Angie, so nice! I'm glad I didn't get hooked though.
We made them together one Christmas! I had a nightmare about mine, and Bob was not very nice!
Awww, the kids loved them though. Especially mine!
Our tree did look really nice every year.
Louise especially seemed to like it.
Although, Bobby used it a fair amount too.
Lin, we only ever seemed to get calls from your family and Teddy.
It had its challenges, like coming home and getting over door thresholds.
It did bring me closer to Jimmy Jr. though, so that was nice.
Aw, some of Tina's work!
Susmita helped me learn my craft
Oh, my angel!
And Logan learned a valuable lesson - do NOT mess with Louise!
The Cutie Patooties - out on their Patooties.
It was nice having a robot sister!
Bobby, you seemed to have some trouble using it.
Don't all fight over it at once.
Who could forget this guy?
So... pink!
Aw, my favorite!
And this one!
I wanted to go to horse camp so much!
I also liked to tell my diary my puns - smart AND sassy.
Jericho and I were best friends.
One of our magical times together
Aw, the burger sign!
I don't think we ever cleaned or maintained that thing.
Genie and I used to watch together.
I had to save the day!
I read some of my best work at school. Mr. Frond seemed surprisingly shook by it.
Love you mom!

my sweetie so pretty!
